articleContentTranslated: Feller wins Flachau slalom Manuel Feller won the men's slalom in Flachau on Saturday. For the Tyrolean, who has already been on the podium five times, it was the first victory in the World Cup.

Feller wins slalom in Flachau With a strong drive, Manuel Feller, after third place in the first round in Flachau, clinched his first victory in the Slalom World Cup. Second place went to Frenchman Clement Noel, which is the third time in a row that he failed to take his half-time lead use.
Marco Schwarz, who celebrated his first World Cup victory in slalom in Adelboden last weekend, went from fifth to third place. Final score in sport.ORF.at/skialpin
